<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If, for example we have:</p>

<pre class="literal">/**
 * My Function
 *
 * @return array
 */
function myFunction() {
    if (something) {
        return array();
    }
    return false;
}</pre>

<p>Because we expected an array, but returned a boolean (it could also be true), the boolean should be taken to be
the status of the request, false = failure, true = success. I think this is a common way to write code :)</p>

<ul><li>Davey</li>
